Halve the @yellow pepper{1/2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1.5}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{5}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Pick the @rosemary{4%sprigs} leaves from their stalks (see ingredients for amount) and finely chop (discard the stalks).

Pour the @water{for the rice} into a #large saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @diced chicken breast{195%g} to the pan, season well with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until brown, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add the @bell pepper{1}(halved and sliced). Fry until starting to soften and colour, about ~{5%minutes}. Add in the garlic, rosemary and @chorizo{60%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{3%minutes}.

Pour the @passata{} and @water{for the sauce} into the pan and bring to the boil. When boiling, lower the heat to medium and leave to simmer, stirring often, until thick and tomatoey, ~{8-10%minutes}. When done, leave on a low heat to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then fold the rice and half of the parsley into the Spanish chicken sauce in the frying pan. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed. Divide between #bowls{} then sprinkle over the remaining parsley. Enjoy!